table.body:
The other person must respond to your nullity petition within 8 days, saying if they agree the marriage should be annulled.

If they agree, you can apply for a 'decree nisi'.

To get a decree nisi, fill in the [application for decree nisi/conditional order.](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=154 "application for decree nisi/conditional order"){:rel="external"}

##Affidavit - sworn statement

You must also fill in an affidavit - a sworn statement that what you said in your nullity petition is true.

There are 2 versions of the affidavit form, depending on whether your marriage is 'void' or 'voidable':

- [affidavit in support of nullity petition - void marriage](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2649 "affidavit in support of nullity petition - void marriage"){:rel="external"}
- [affidavit in support of nullity petition - voidable marriage](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2650 "affidavit in support of nullity petition - voidable marriage"){:rel="external"}

%You must get the affidavit witnessed by a member of court staff or a solicitor (a solicitor may charge a fee).%

A decree nisi costs £45.
